# ELEFRIENDS SRI LANKA - Safari Tour Booking Website

This plan details the folder structure and setup for a high-performance Next.js 14 application tailored for safari tour bookings, adhering to a premium dark-themed glassmorphism aesthetic.

## Proposed File Structure

We will use the **Next.js App Router** with the `src` directory to keep our components and logic separated from configuration files.

```text
elefriends-safari/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ public/                 # Static assets (images, icons)
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ locales/            # Translation files if not using next-intl built-in dictionary
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ src/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app/                # Next.js App Router
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ [locale]/       # Dynamic route segment for internationalization
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ admin/      # Admin Dashboard (Protected Route)
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ bookings/
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ tours/
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ page.tsx
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ checkout/   # Booking & Payment Flow
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ page.tsx
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ tours/      # Safari Packages
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ [id]/
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ page.tsx
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ page.tsx
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ layout.tsx  # Global layout (Nav, Footer, Providers)
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ page.tsx    # Landing Page (Hero, Destination Cards)
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ api/            # API Routes
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ checkout/   # Stripe/PayHere webhooks and checkout init
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ webhooks/
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ globals.css     # Global styles & Tailwind layers (Glassmorphism utils)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ components/         # Reusable UI components
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ ui/             # Base UI elements (Buttons, Inputs, Cards)
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ layout/         # Navbar, Footer, Sidebar
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ home/           # HeroSection, DestinationCards
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ booking/        # BookingForm, PaymentSummary
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ admin/          # Admin tables, forms
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ lib/                # Utility functions & Configurations
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ supabase/       # Supabase client setup (or prisma/)
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ stripe/         # Stripe client setup (or payhere/)
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ utils.ts        # Helper functions (classnames, formatting)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ messages/           # next-intl translation dictionaries (en.json, de.json, fr.json)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ types/              # TypeScript interfaces (Tour, Booking, User)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ i18n.ts             # next-intl configuration
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ middleware.ts       # Middleware for i18n routing and Auth protection
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ .env.local              # Environment variables
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ next.config.mjs         # Next.js configuration
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ tailwind.config.ts      # Tailwind CSS configuration
в””в”Ђв”Ђ package.json            # Project dependencies
```

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Please review the file structure above. Let me know if you would like me to proceed with generating the boilerplate code.

I have a couple of quick questions before we start the boilerplate:
1. Is **Stripe** or **PayHere** preferred for the payment gateway?
2. Should we use **Supabase** or **Prisma** (with another Postgres provider) for the backend?

## Verification Plan
After scaffolding the project, we will run the local dev server using `npm run dev` and ensure the Next.js shell and basic routing are functional at `http://localhost:3000`. We will also configure the initial Tailwind theme and test that the dark mode and glassmorphism utilities compile properly.
